<h1>Our Concept</h1>
<div class="banner">
  We use face-analyzing technology to determine the effectiveness of our images.
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="column left">
    <img
      id="left-arrow-1"
      class="left-arrow"
      src="green-arrow.png"
      alt="Image not found"
    />
    <img
      id="left-arrow-2"
      class="left-arrow"
      src="green-arrow.png"
      alt="Image not found"
    />
  </div>
  <div class="column center" style="text-align: center;">
    <div
      class="step"
      style="background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(133,220,184,0.5) 0%, rgba(133,220,184,1) 23%);"
    >
      Our face-analyzer <b>interprets</b> the emotions on each user's face when
      presented with an image.
    </div>
    <div class="step" style="background-color: #e8a87c;">
      We then <b>rank</b> the emotions evoked for that user on that image, and
      factor those rankings into the results collected from past users.
    </div>
    <div
      class="step"
      style="background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(133,220,184,0.5) 0%, rgba(133,220,184,1) 23%);"
    >
      Users can see how their emotions <b>compare</b> to those of other users
      who saw the same image.
    </div>
    <div class="step" style="background-color: #e8a87c;">
      Content creators can see how <b>effective</b> their media is at evoking
      intended emotions.
    </div>
  </div>
